objects.name: goofy guineapig
objects.description: A persistent Windows backdoor with HTTPS C2 communications. It masquerades as a Google update component and maintains persistence as a Windows service.

objects.name: T1543.003
objects.description: Create or Modify System Process: Windows Service. The malware maintains persistence by creating a Windows service.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location. The malware masquerades as a legitimate Google update component.

objects.name: T1497.003
objects.description: Virtualization/Sandbox Evasion: Time Based Evasion. The malware checks the time register twice for a delay of more than 100 milliseconds and will not continue execution if more time has elapsed.

objects.name: T1218.011
objects.description: System Binary Proxy Execution: Rundll32. The malware uses the legitimate Microsoft binary rundll32.exe to execute itself.

objects.name: T1071.001
objects.description: Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols. The malware uses HTTPS for its C2 communications.

objects.name: T1574.002
objects.description: Hijack Execution Flow: DLL Side-Loading. The malware loads a malicious DLL that is sideloaded by the legitimate GoogleUpdate.exe executable.

objects.name: T1055.012
objects.description: Process Injection: Process Hollowing. The malware performs process hollowing on the dllhost.exe binary to inject its payload.

objects.name: T1082
objects.description: System Information Discovery. The malware collects information about the infected machine, including the operating system caption, antivirus product display name, adapters information, host and host name, and computer name.
